fields.description:
Docs - Correct incorrect references to stylesheets in documentation segments

Steps to reproduce:
1. Open (*multiple locations*)
*1)* [https://www.ag-grid.com/react-data-grid/modules/#cssscss-paths|https://www.ag-grid.com/react-data-grid/modules/#cssscss-paths]
*2)* [https://www.ag-grid.com/react-grid/getting-started/#customise-the-theme-look-1|https://www.ag-grid.com/react-grid/getting-started/#customise-the-theme-look-1]


2. Take a look at the code segment specifically the paths to the CSS files

*Actual:*
import "./node_modules/@ag-grid-community/core/dist/styles/ag-grid.css";
import "./node_modules/@ag-grid-community/core/dist/styles/ag-theme-alpine.css";

*Correct:*
@import "~ag-grid-community/src/styles/ag-grid.scss";@import "~ag-grid-community/src/styles/ag-theme-alpine/sass/ag-theme-alpine-mixin.scss";

Referencing the CSS using the actual paths above breaks samples, as shown here:
[https://stackblitz.com/edit/react-xqdduj?file=src%2FApp.js|https://stackblitz.com/edit/react-xqdduj?file=src%2FApp.js]

Typing - Correct typing for return value of CellRendererSelectorFunc to also include undefined

export interface CellRendererSelectorFunc extends SelectorFunc {
(params: ICellRendererParams): CellRendererSelectorResult;
}
export interface CellEditorSelectorFunc extends SelectorFunc {
(params: ICellEditorParams): CellEditorSelectorResult;
}
export interface CellRendererSelectorResult {
component?: {
new (): ICellRendererComp;
} | ICellRendererFunc | string;
frameworkComponent?: any;
params?: any;
}

However, the *CellEditorSelectorFunc* requires *CellRendererSelectorResult* as return value. But according to your example for *CellRendererSelector*(https://www.ag-grid.com/react-data-grid/row-pinning/#example), it can be returned with undefined if there is no variant for that function.

This is why the return typing should include undefined:

*Current:*
export interface CellRendererSelectorFunc extends SelectorFunc {
(params: ICellRendererParams): CellRendererSelectorResult;
}

should be changed below for example

*Correct:*
export interface CellRendererSelectorFunc extends SelectorFunc {
(params: ICellRendererParams): CellRendererSelectorResult | undefined;
}

Added api and columnApi to all 4 of the navigation methods. 

* {noformat}    navigateToNextHeader?: (params: NavigateToNextHeaderParams) => HeaderPosition;
    tabToNextHeader?: (params: TabToNextHeaderParams) => HeaderPosition;

    navigateToNextCell?: (params: NavigateToNextCellParams) => CellPosition;
    tabToNextCell?: (params: TabToNextCellParams) => CellPosition;{noformat}

API - Standardize the use of colKey parameter across all methods in ColumnAPI

We are using 'key' and 'colKey' interchangeably across our columnApi methods. 
In our docs we refer to *colKey* as the argument to methods in ColumnAPI:
https://www.ag-grid.com/javascript-grid-column-api/#reference-api

However, in the prototype of these methods, we're using *key* instead - see below:
public setColumnWidth(key: string | Column, newWidth: number, finished: boolean = true): void {
 this.columnController.setColumnWidths([{key, newWidth}], false, finished);
}
public setColumnWidths(columnWidths: {key: string | Column, newWidth: number}[], finished: boolean = true): void {
 this.columnController.setColumnWidths(columnWidths, false, finished);
}

*Key* and *colKey* both refer to the same type, i.e. Column | string  

We need to standardise to colKey across all methods

fields.customfield_10522:
An example of a typed tooltip in the Grid is as follows:<br/>
<pre>
import React, {forwardRef, ForwardRefRenderFunction, useImperativeHandle} from 'react';
import {ITooltipParams} from "@ag-grid-community/core";
import {ITooltipReactComp} from "@ag-grid-community/react";

interface MyTooltipParams extends ITooltipParams {
    color?: string
}

const CustomTooltip: ForwardRefRenderFunction<ITooltipReactComp, MyTooltipParams> = (props, ref) => {
    const data = props.api!.getDisplayedRowAtIndex(props.rowIndex!)!.data;

    useImperativeHandle((ref), () => ({
        getReactContainerClasses() {
            return ['custom-tooltip'];
        },
    }));

    return (
        <div
            className="custom-tooltip"
            style={{backgroundColor: props.color || 'white'}}
        >
            <p>
                <span>{data.athlete}</span>
            </p>
            <p>
                <span>Country: </span> {data.country}
            </p>
            <p>
                <span>Total: </span> {data.total}
            </p>
        </div>
    );
};

export default forwardRef(CustomTooltip);
</pre>

